01:39.000 --> 01:45.793
Americans are obese, drunk,
and addicted to pills.

01:45.896 --> 01:48.034
Everyone is hooked on something.

01:48.137 --> 01:50.379
Addiction in this country
is an epidemic.

01:50.482 --> 01:54.551
And it is fantastic
for business.

01:54.655 --> 01:57.620
90 percent of shopping
is done by shopaholics.

01:57.724 --> 02:00.517
90 percent of chocolate
is consumed by chocoholics.

02:00.620 --> 02:02.344
90 percent of alcohol
is consumed

02:02.448 --> 02:04.586
by people addicted to alcohol.

02:04.689 --> 02:06.344
That's why I'm announcing
an open call

02:06.448 --> 02:09.620
for pitches on new addictions.

02:09.724 --> 02:12.275
So, let's put on
our thinking caps.

02:12.379 --> 02:15.172
Kate: All right, let's open
the room to addiction.

02:15.275 --> 02:17.000
Matt, that's gross.

02:17.103 --> 02:19.275
There's no reason to have
a visible pimple as an adult.

02:19.379 --> 02:21.344
Use some concealer
for Christ's sake.

02:21.448 --> 02:22.379
I don't wear makeup.

02:22.482 --> 02:24.034
Well,
then you're an idiot.

02:24.137 --> 02:25.965
-Wait, do you wear makeup?
-Of course.

02:26.068 --> 02:27.758
Hot people do better
at business.

02:27.862 --> 02:29.034
I've never noticed.

02:29.137 --> 02:30.275
That's because
I'm a master of the craft

02:30.379 --> 02:31.965
and you're blinded
by my beauty.

02:32.068 --> 02:34.206
You look good.
I've always thought that.

02:34.310 --> 02:35.586
Painkillers can be good.

02:35.689 --> 02:37.068
Do you have any specific
painkillers that you prefer?

02:37.172 --> 02:38.413
Kate:
Have you used Fentanyl?

02:38.517 --> 02:40.068
I don't know
what the names are.

02:40.172 --> 02:41.344
I just --
I know the colors.

02:41.448 --> 02:42.758
Do you think
you could be convinced

02:42.862 --> 02:43.758
to start
wearing makeup?

02:43.862 --> 02:45.413
[ Scoffs ]
No way.

02:45.517 --> 02:47.103
Because you're insecure
about your masculinity.

02:47.206 --> 02:48.827
I'm not insecure
about my masculinity.

02:48.931 --> 02:51.827
I just don't think anybody
should wear makeup personally.

02:51.931 --> 02:53.068
Not even women.

02:53.172 --> 02:54.448
If women liked
the way they look,

02:54.551 --> 02:56.758
the entire American economy
would collapse.

02:56.862 --> 02:58.620
The fact that Hampton DeVille
isn't capitalizing

02:58.724 --> 03:00.551
on men's shame
is a huge mistake.

03:00.655 --> 03:04.068
Kate and I will be pre-screening
the pitches on Wednesday

03:04.172 --> 03:05.517
in the Oasis
conference room --

03:05.620 --> 03:07.620
The Oasis is too small.
Let's do the Driskoll.

03:07.724 --> 03:11.482
But I already booked
the Oasis room.
Who cares?

03:11.586 --> 03:14.241
It takes one e-mail
to change the reservation.

03:14.344 --> 03:17.758
We'll see everyone
Wednesday in the Driskoll.

03:17.862 --> 03:20.413
Oh, damn it,
I'm late for my ZenCycle class.

03:20.517 --> 03:21.724
If I'm not screamed at

03:21.827 --> 03:23.310
by a tiny woman
at least once a day,

03:23.413 --> 03:24.965
I simply cannot function.

03:25.068 --> 03:26.310
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:26.413 --> 03:29.448
Kate, I understand
you're tired today,

03:29.551 --> 03:32.827
but you should
really watch your tone.

03:34.241 --> 03:35.206
My tone?

03:35.310 --> 03:36.620
You have a sharp,
cutting tone

03:36.724 --> 03:39.310
that marginalizes
and diminishes people.

03:39.413 --> 03:41.310
Is this about
the Oasis room?

03:41.413 --> 03:42.689
Don't be so sensitive.

03:42.793 --> 03:45.206
Ooh, do you hear
your tone right now?

03:45.310 --> 03:46.413
You might not.

03:46.517 --> 03:48.655
It's combative.
It's aggressive.

03:48.758 --> 03:50.379
And honestly,
if I didn't know you,

03:50.482 --> 03:53.758
I'd feel physically
unsafe right now.

03:53.862 --> 03:55.724
Whereas my tone is calm

03:55.827 --> 03:57.793
because I'm in control
of my emotions,

03:57.896 --> 04:03.551
and I will never,
ever let them loose.

04:03.655 --> 04:06.000
You have a vein popping out
of your forehead.

04:06.103 --> 04:08.620
I'm telling you all this
for your benefit, Kate.

04:08.724 --> 04:15.862
♪♪

04:15.965 --> 04:17.793
-What?
-Nothing.

04:17.896 --> 04:21.689
It's just, um, you don't
wear makeup, do you?

04:21.793 --> 04:24.172
Every evening,
I destroy my face,

04:24.275 --> 04:27.000
and every morning,
I rebuilt it anew.

04:27.103 --> 04:29.862
Really? I always thought
you were a natural beauty.

04:29.965 --> 04:32.206
Doesn't matter what
Mother Nature gives you --

04:32.310 --> 04:34.068
all women are taught
at a young age

04:34.172 --> 04:35.620
to hate
the way they look.

04:35.724 --> 04:37.620
Paige, you don't
wear makeup, do you?

04:37.724 --> 04:38.862
[ Scoffs ]

04:38.965 --> 04:40.931
Why don't you ask
the 200,000 makeup addicts

04:41.034 --> 04:42.482
who watch
my makeup tutorials?

04:42.586 --> 04:45.931
Only men can get away with
looking like shit every day.

04:46.034 --> 04:48.172
You think I look
like shit?

04:48.275 --> 04:50.655
You have...
flaws.

04:50.758 --> 04:52.206
What are they?

04:52.310 --> 04:54.689
♪♪

04:54.793 --> 04:57.310
Matt,
you have to understand,

04:57.413 --> 05:00.655
if we tell you,
there's no going back.

05:01.586 --> 05:04.758
Pick the azure eyeliner,
and the conversation ends here.

05:04.862 --> 05:08.482
You wake up in your bed
and believe you're beautiful.

05:08.586 --> 05:10.931
Pick this scarlet lip liner,
and we'll show you

05:11.034 --> 05:14.172
how deep the rabbit hole
of insecurity goes.

05:14.275 --> 05:21.448
♪♪

05:23.275 --> 05:25.482
Your pores are visible
from four feet away.Your skin is both oily
and flaky.

05:25.586 --> 05:27.413
I don't understand
how that's possible.

05:27.517 --> 05:29.310
You remind me of the Green Giant
from the green bean can.Your face has a dull,

05:29.413 --> 05:31.068
dingy yellow
undertone to it --The bags underneath your eyes

05:31.172 --> 05:32.551
are like deflated basketballs...

05:32.655 --> 05:34.793
-The beard's not...
-...like, inbred or something.

05:34.896 --> 05:36.586
Men are ugly.

05:36.689 --> 05:38.344
They just don't know it yet.

05:38.448 --> 05:41.137
You, sir, did you know
that you're ugly?

05:41.241 --> 05:42.482
Well, it's true.

05:42.586 --> 05:45.241
But I've got a cure
for your ugly face --

05:45.344 --> 05:46.793
male makeup.

05:46.896 --> 05:49.793
Matt: Jake,
will you help me?

05:49.896 --> 05:52.551
I need help.

05:52.655 --> 05:54.551
I knew this day
would come.

05:54.655 --> 05:56.551
Come here, boy.[ Cries softly ]

05:57.758 --> 06:00.724
You look so bad, bro.
I'll fix you up good.

06:03.068 --> 06:06.241
I want to tell you a story
about my grandfather.

06:06.344 --> 06:08.965
My grandfather was never
a beautiful man.

06:09.068 --> 06:11.241
He always struggled
with his looks.

06:11.344 --> 06:14.862
But then, one day, I saw him
at his most handsome --

06:14.965 --> 06:18.655
in a casket,
covered in makeup.

06:18.758 --> 06:22.551
The beauty industry
pulls in $430 billion

06:22.655 --> 06:24.931
in sales every single year.

06:25.034 --> 06:26.793
Who are these sales to?

06:26.896 --> 06:28.310
Women.

06:28.413 --> 06:32.241
By my estimation, women are
only half the human population.

06:32.344 --> 06:34.206
The other half?

06:34.310 --> 06:36.551
Men.
Guys.

06:36.655 --> 06:39.034
Fellas.
Daddy-Os.

06:39.137 --> 06:42.034
Let's take a look at Matt.

06:42.137 --> 06:44.827
Matt used to think
he was a natural beauty.

06:44.931 --> 06:47.517
Until this past week,
no one had ever thought

06:47.620 --> 06:51.517
to tell him that he is,
in fact, an uggo.

06:51.620 --> 06:53.965
However,
with the power of makeup,

06:54.068 --> 06:57.206
I have managed
to transform this pauper...

06:57.310 --> 06:58.448
into a prince.

06:58.551 --> 07:00.206
[ Executives gasp ]

07:00.310 --> 07:01.862
[ Chuckles ]

07:01.965 --> 07:05.034
Makeup has given him
a newfound confidence.

07:05.137 --> 07:08.000
We have forgiven
his many intellectual

07:08.103 --> 07:09.103
and personal failings

07:09.206 --> 07:13.000
because, quite simply,
he looks stunning.

07:13.103 --> 07:16.000
I believe that
with a little convincing,

07:16.103 --> 07:19.103
we could not only get men
to start wearing makeup,

07:19.206 --> 07:22.034
we could get them addicted

07:22.137 --> 07:27.620
and change the face of
the beauty industry forever.

07:27.724 --> 07:29.000
[ Cheers and applause ]

07:29.103 --> 07:31.448
Great stuff.Hot dog!

07:31.551 --> 07:34.724
[ Laughs ]

07:38.482 --> 07:40.137
I think we're all
in agreement here

07:40.241 --> 07:41.275
that the stand-out pitch

07:41.379 --> 07:42.586
was Jake's Male Makeup idea,

07:42.689 --> 07:45.068
the first good idea
he's had

07:45.172 --> 07:46.344
maybe ever?
Right.

07:46.448 --> 07:47.896
I think we should
all work together

07:48.000 --> 07:48.862
to develop this idea.

07:48.965 --> 07:50.310
Well, I think Christian
will want

07:50.413 --> 07:51.965
more than one idea
to choose from,

07:52.068 --> 07:54.206
so how 'bout I lead
the male makeup team --

07:54.310 --> 07:56.172
after all, I am a male --

07:56.275 --> 08:00.482
and you can take your pick
of the other great ideas?

08:00.586 --> 08:02.758
But seeing as
I'm the only one here

08:02.862 --> 08:06.103
who actually wears
makeup every single day --

08:06.206 --> 08:08.758
You wear makeup?
Huh.

08:08.862 --> 08:11.241
I always thought you were
a natural beauty.

08:11.344 --> 08:12.689
Guess not.

08:12.793 --> 08:15.241
My point is, I think
I'm more equipped

08:15.344 --> 08:16.793
to lead
the male makeup team.

08:16.896 --> 08:18.413
You think I don't know
about makeup?
Mnh-mnh.

08:18.517 --> 08:20.344
I bet I know
just as much as you do.

08:20.448 --> 08:22.896
-Let's find out.
-Let's.

08:23.000 --> 08:27.827
How much does this
lipstick cost?

08:27.931 --> 08:29.758
Okay. [ Clears throat ]
What do we got here?

08:29.862 --> 08:33.310
This looks small,
so really cheap plastic.

08:33.413 --> 08:34.793
[ Sniffs ]
Smells domestic

08:34.896 --> 08:37.103
as opposed
to European imported.

08:37.206 --> 08:40.413
So, I want to say,
89 cents.

08:40.517 --> 08:43.724
No!
79 cents.

08:44.689 --> 08:45.413
$60!

08:45.517 --> 08:47.827
-What?
-Jesus Christ!

08:47.931 --> 08:52.413
You clearly know
nothing about makeup.

08:52.517 --> 08:54.379
Kate, I didn't want to have
to call this out

08:54.482 --> 08:57.034
in front of everyone,
but...

08:57.137 --> 08:58.551
there's that tone
again!

08:58.655 --> 08:59.793
There's nothing

08:59.896 --> 09:02.551
wrong with my tone.Let's find out.

09:02.655 --> 09:05.758
Who here has ever felt
silenced or diminished

09:05.862 --> 09:08.655
by Kate's harsh,
knifey tone?

09:10.517 --> 09:13.000
Oh.
Every last one.

09:15.793 --> 09:16.931
Fine.

09:17.034 --> 09:19.379
You take
the male makeup team...Okay.

09:19.482 --> 09:23.172
...and I'll take...
nicotine toothpaste.

09:23.275 --> 09:24.586
Good one.
Great.

09:24.689 --> 09:27.379
So, who wants to be
on the male makeup team?

09:27.482 --> 09:29.689
Oh.
All of 'em again.

09:30.793 --> 09:34.000
Grace, I'd like to file
a complaint against John.

09:34.103 --> 09:36.517
He just filed
a complaint against you.

09:36.620 --> 09:39.413
Really?
About what?

09:39.517 --> 09:41.000
Your aggressive tone.

09:41.103 --> 09:42.413
That little bitch.

09:42.517 --> 09:43.793
Don't take it
personally.

09:43.896 --> 09:46.206
Men have been complaining
about women's tones

09:46.310 --> 09:50.655
ever since women started working
at Hampton DeVille in 1993.

09:50.758 --> 09:53.827
Have other men complained
about my tone?

09:53.931 --> 09:56.103
A few...

09:56.206 --> 09:57.931
dozen...

09:58.034 --> 09:59.310
hundred.

09:59.413 --> 10:02.137
A few dozen hundred?

10:02.241 --> 10:03.517
Let me see what they said.

10:03.620 --> 10:06.413
Kate, if I let you read
what your male co-workers

10:06.517 --> 10:10.275
have said about you,
there is no going back.

10:10.379 --> 10:11.758
[ Thunder rumbles ]

10:11.862 --> 10:14.655
If you pick the blue pen,
you'll wake up --

10:14.758 --> 10:17.103
Just show it to me!
[ Sighs ]

10:17.206 --> 10:19.137
-Her tone was too harsh...
-Feel emasculated...

10:19.241 --> 10:21.068
-It was the way she said it...
-She's taller than me...

10:21.172 --> 10:22.517
-Cuts like a dagger...
-Knifey...

10:22.620 --> 10:23.862
-Like a sword...
-Piercing...

10:23.965 --> 10:25.344
-Like a knife-hatchet...
-Knife-blade...

10:25.448 --> 10:26.793
Thank you.

10:26.896 --> 10:29.413
It's always so cold
in this building.

10:29.517 --> 10:33.068
The temperature in offices is
set to accommodate men in suits

10:33.172 --> 10:35.655
who get to keep
the hair on their bodies.

10:35.758 --> 10:39.379
But luckily, I have developed
ways of adapting.

10:39.482 --> 10:41.965
It is always shocking
to be reminded

10:42.068 --> 10:45.034
how pathetically sensitive
the men in this office are.

10:45.137 --> 10:48.206
That's why I've compiled
a list of the best tones

10:48.310 --> 10:50.413
to use for men in the office.

10:50.517 --> 10:52.724
I could teach you,
and, in exchange,

10:52.827 --> 10:55.310
maybe you could pull
some strings with the guy

10:55.413 --> 10:57.241
who controls
the AC around here.

10:57.344 --> 10:58.724
Deal.

10:58.827 --> 11:01.931
The most popular tone
among men in the office

11:02.034 --> 11:06.103
is one I like to call
"Horny Toddler."

11:06.206 --> 11:14.068
♪♪

11:14.172 --> 11:16.896
We are going to manipulate
male insecurity

11:17.000 --> 11:18.482
through a propaganda campaign.

11:18.586 --> 11:20.965
We'll target entertainment
for boys as young as possible

11:21.068 --> 11:22.620
so they'll be hooked for life.

11:22.724 --> 11:25.137
If little boys don't feel
like unlovable garbage,

11:25.241 --> 11:27.068
we haven't done our jobs!

11:27.172 --> 11:28.620
Try Shy Ghost.

11:28.724 --> 11:30.758
[ Breathy voice ] I hope
it's not totally weird

11:30.862 --> 11:32.034
that I'm saying this,

11:32.137 --> 11:34.034
but you look
really good today.

11:34.137 --> 11:37.482
Remember, tone isn't just
about the pitch of your voice.

11:37.586 --> 11:40.896
Make sure to start and end
every sentence with an apology.

11:41.000 --> 11:43.241
[ Normal voice ] I'm sorry.Perfect.

11:43.344 --> 11:44.827
Hi, guys.
It's Paige.

11:44.931 --> 11:47.758
And there are two types
of people in this world --

11:47.862 --> 11:49.482
those who know
how to contour,

11:49.586 --> 11:52.137
and those who are abandoned
by everyone that they love.

11:52.241 --> 11:54.862
Jake: We want to create
a culture of shame.

11:54.965 --> 11:57.758
So, what are some things
you feel ashamed of?

11:57.862 --> 12:00.551
-Redness. A lot of redness.
-My son.

12:00.655 --> 12:02.862
Let's stick to physical
attributes for now.

12:02.965 --> 12:05.724
All right,
my son's weak arms.

12:06.551 --> 12:08.103
Okay.

12:08.206 --> 12:09.517
[ Breathes sharply ]

12:09.620 --> 12:11.517
Hey, Matt, I'm sorry,

12:11.620 --> 12:14.655
but you look, like,
so super good today.

12:14.758 --> 12:15.931
[ Chuckling ]
I'm sorry.

12:16.034 --> 12:18.482
Thanks, Kate.
I really appreciate that.

12:18.586 --> 12:20.862
And I'm sorry,
but would you be willing

12:20.965 --> 12:23.068
to maybe
work late tonight?

12:23.172 --> 12:24.862
Yeah, of course.
I'd love to help out.

12:24.965 --> 12:27.206
You look like you could
use the break anyway.

12:27.310 --> 12:28.931
Jake: We need to normalize
makeup for men

12:29.034 --> 12:31.724
by associating it
with things men already like.

12:31.827 --> 12:33.724
So, what do men like?

12:33.827 --> 12:35.137
-World War II?
-Yep.

12:35.241 --> 12:36.655
-Sex.
-Yeah.

12:36.758 --> 12:39.172
-Football.
-Exotic jungle birds.

12:39.275 --> 12:40.862
Okay, what else?

12:40.965 --> 12:43.379
Keeping secrets
from my fucking wife!

12:43.482 --> 12:46.413
Jake, it's
"exotic jungle" birds.

12:46.517 --> 12:49.034
♪♪

12:49.137 --> 12:51.586
Jessica: Hey, Matt,
nice contouring.

12:51.689 --> 12:53.103
Thanks, Jessica.

12:53.206 --> 12:55.413
Have you thought about doing
something with your lashes?

12:55.517 --> 12:57.896
-Yeah.
-Be really cute.

12:58.000 --> 13:05.827
♪♪

13:05.931 --> 13:07.206
Dying ballerina!

13:07.310 --> 13:10.103
[ Weakly ] Sorry, I'm like,
so totally sorry.

13:10.206 --> 13:11.620
Anthropomorphized
sparrow!

13:11.724 --> 13:13.034
[ Squeaky voice ]
I'm sure you have, like,

13:13.137 --> 13:14.413
a million different things
to do than talk to me today,

13:14.517 --> 13:16.241
but [ Normal voice ]
a lot of women in the office

13:16.344 --> 13:18.206
have been talking about
how it's, like, too cold.

13:18.310 --> 13:21.068
So, I was wondering
if you could do me, like,

13:21.172 --> 13:25.068
a tiny, huge favor and maybe
make it a little bit warmer.

13:25.172 --> 13:26.241
Sorry.

13:26.344 --> 13:31.965
♪♪

13:33.206 --> 13:35.206
Announcer:
Whether it's mid-game,

13:35.241 --> 13:37.413
mid-east, or mid-ages...

13:37.517 --> 13:38.896
[ Gun cocks, gunshots ]

13:39.000 --> 13:42.000
[ Cat yowls ]...you need to bring your armor.

13:42.103 --> 13:46.137
Whatever your battlefield,
we've got your back...

13:46.241 --> 13:47.793
and your front.

13:47.896 --> 13:51.275
R-More -- wear it proud.

13:51.379 --> 13:53.206
[ Gunshot ]

13:53.310 --> 13:55.275
Jake: We want to get
your honest feedback.

13:55.379 --> 13:57.793
Would you try R-More?

13:59.310 --> 14:00.793
Well, I...

14:00.896 --> 14:04.379
I have always hated these
dark circles under my eyes.

14:04.482 --> 14:05.448
Could R-More
help me with that?

14:05.551 --> 14:07.172
-Definitely.
-Absolutely.

14:07.275 --> 14:08.896
I've been trying to get
a promotion at work.

14:09.000 --> 14:10.827
Maybe this could
give me a leg up.

14:10.931 --> 14:12.310
Maybe so.
And good luck.

14:12.413 --> 14:13.482
Chad: I use Chap Stick,

14:13.586 --> 14:15.724
